  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior M&E Engineer (Top-Down)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Managing M&E installations while working in coordination with top-down construction\ntechniques, which often involves integrating services as levels are completed\nconsecutively.</li><li>Overseeing subcontractors to ensure compliance with design drawings, safety regulations,\nand quality standards (e.g., CONQUAS).</li><li>CoordinatingM&E shop drawings and Building Information Modelling (BIM) models to\nresolve clashes with architectural and structural elements.</li><li>Managing inspections and approvals with authorities (BCA, SCDF, PUB, NEA) leading to\nTemporary Occupation Permit (TOP) and Certificate of Statutory Completion\n(CSC).</li><li>Establishing the sequence of works, managing variations (VOs), tracking progress, and\nensuring on-time delivery.</li><li>Managing the testing, commissioning, and final handover of all MEP systems. </li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or Building Services recognized by\nthe PE Board.</li><li>Minimum 5 years M&E experience in large building or infrastructure projects.</li><li>Proven experience in large-scale projects (arena, stadium, convention centre, airport, hospital\npreferred).</li><li>Strong knowledge<strong> </strong>of ACMV / HVAC systems, Electrical & ELV systems, Fire protection systems, Plumbing & drainage and BMS integration.</li></ul>",
